name: "No, Charles."
description:
Photography of things that do not exist for more than a fleeting moment, undefined by time and space. Nonsensical environments where logic and reality do not hold sway. Accidental imagery relying more on chance, whim, obtuse thought patterns and often a sense of play. The relentless search for the lightness and darkness within life.

"No, Charles!" refers to an "Oh Shit moment."
If you were drowning, how deep is the ocean?
